The paper deals with image synthesis, specifically for person images conditioned on arbitrary poses. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also addresses challenges related to geometric variability and spatial displacements, which could be categorized under graphics (cs.GR). The proposed Soft-Gated Warping Generative Adversarial Network (Warping-GAN) involves learning feature-level mapping, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions human perceptual studies, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for image synthesis, which could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
